		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.55]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I recommend the following (not the exact words use /do # for the appropriate skill)<br>a) &quot;evade + macro&quot;<br>/attack off<br>/hide (evade)<br>/pickpockets or /beg when pp maxed for that level<br>/attack on<br><br>b) &quot;backstab + macro&quot;<br>/backstab<br>/sense traps<br>/disarm trap<br>/loc<br><br>By including beg, pickpocket, sense and disarm traps in these macros you will get those skills up while doing the every day combat actions you do normally and not require extra actions. You will need the pickpocket for the Epic, sense and disarm traps for LDON and there is an uber charm based on a couple of skills which include begging so might as well get that up as well.<br><br>Just a side note , while actually in a LDON dungeon you will encounter actual traps and you might want to disable the sense traps portion as you will spin towards the trap in battle which may make you not see your target. I would leave disarm traps, but do not use right next to a container. I usually leave a backstab button on hotkeys for direct backstab so I can see when timer is up. I use that button when near containers or near traps that make me spin and I do not change the macro.<br> <br>I include /loc in bs macro because it enable an easy to hit loc hotkey for those moments I am about to die and will need to know where corpse is, w/o using up a hotkey spot.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Lord McSean Shadowraider level 65 Halfling Rogue,<br>Cullum level 37 Dwarf Paladin<br>Necrosaurous level 27 Iksar Necromancer<br>Leapof Faith level 24 Froglok Cleric<br>Xauvian Level 1 Trader Mule Extraordinaire<br>XEGONY SERVER</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
